.Dd $Mdocdate: June 5 2013 $
.Dt WCSSPN 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm wcsspn
.Nd span a wide string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In wchar.h
.Ft size_t
.Fn wcsspn "const wchar_t *s" "const wchar_t *charset"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn wcsspn
function spans the initial part of the wide string
.Fa s
as long as the wide characters from
.Fa s
occur in the wide string
.Fa charset .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn wcsspn
function returns the number of wide characters spanned.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr strspn 3 ,
.Xr wcschr 3 ,
.Xr wcscspn 3 ,
.Xr wcspbrk 3 ,
.Xr wcsrchr 3 ,
.Xr wcsstr 3 ,
.Xr wcstok 3 ,
.Xr wmemchr 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn wcsspn
function conforms to
.St -isoC-99
and was first introduced in
.St -isoC-amd1 .
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn wcsspn
function was ported from
.Nx
and first appeared in
.Ox 3.8 .
